Subsequent to his conviction and sentence, Sewnarain lodged a successful appeal in the Pietermaritzburg High Court where his conviction and sentence was set aside. AdChoicesADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads
A new trial was ordered.

In March 2017 Sewnarain applied for bail pending his new trial which was denied by Magistrate Anand Maharaj. 
His new trial began in March 2018. 

He was found guilty in the Durban High Court. 
